description.value: Fragment of a vessel made of calcite. The base is flat and at a height of 0.6 a circumferential indentation defines the edge. The body is tapered towards the base with the maximum diameter at the shoulders at which the vessel is broken off. An area at the shoulder is visible where a handle is broken off. The handle had a width of 1.3 and a height of 0.8 cm. The upper part of the vessel is not preserved. There is a partially smoothed edge at the top edge where the vessel is broken off. This seems to be traces of reuse, maybe for polishing or other use.

description.value: An open vessel of coarse red siltware pottery, with a rounded base and near vertical sides, which rise to a rounded rim. There is a moulding around the exterior below the rim and also a shallow groove some 3cm lower. The base is perforated by a small hole, apparently part of the original design, since it is surrounded by a low rim. The vessel exhibits irragularities: the level of the rim varies and the profiles of the sides are not regular. The exterior bears substantial remains of a slip, which varies in colour from pink to pale cream.

description.value: Vessel with rounded base of rough brown ware pottery originally with a single loop handle over the top, made of Nile silt fabric with large organic voids and white mineral grit. Surface is worn; originally self-slipped reddish with many fire cloud stains, burnished vertically. Rim is pinched irregularly, rising up around the points of attachment for the handle, scars of which remain.  Marks from manufacture are visible on interior walls as finger impressions made during the attachment of the coiled walls to the mould-made base.

description.value: Fragment of a faience vessel, complete profile preserved. Light green glaze inside and outside with a black geometrical decoration outside. Partly chipped on surface. The base is flat but is running down to the centre of the vessel, the edges at base and rim are protruding outwards slightly, getting thinner in the middle part of the wall. Flat rim with black decoration in form of a band. At the outer side a rectangle that is divided into four triangles, each having a black circle or oval dot. Left of the rectangle a vertical line.
